    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "> Would it be fair to say that (for phase 0 at least) the logic is roughly equivalent to removing the delay in process_exit_queue and doubling the delay in prepare_validator_for_withdrawal? \r\n\r\nI don't think it's *quite* equivalent to either of those. If `x` is the queue length, then `max(x, 2)`, `max(x, 1) + 1` and `x + 2` are all different functions.\r\n\r\n> On this topic, do we want to change the rate limiting logic based on this Ethresear.ch post?\r\n\r\nMy heart wants to, my \"let's do things now as an investment in making future phases easier\" side also does, but my \"we have to ship and we need to ban making nontrivial new changes at some point\" side says no.....",
